        {
            "Text": "This data layer shows an animated timelapse of refugee migration from 2000 to 2016. Each dot represents an individual person leaving a country due to conflict or persecution. The dots flow from the center of the departing country to the center of the arriving country, changing color from yellow to red. This data does not include internal displacement or people leaving their country for work or food insecurity.",
