            "Pause": false,
            "StartFrame": "2011",
            "LoopRange": ["2011", "2015"],
            "Layers": ["show-annual-refugees"],
            "Map": "dark-base"
        },
        {
            "Text": "While there has been a historic number of people seeking asylum in European Countries such as Germany and Sweden, most of the Syrian refugees are fleeing to neighboring countries: Turkey, Jordan, and Lebanon. This further perpetuates the crisis, as these countries lack resources to accommodate incoming refugees.",
            "BoundingBox": {
